\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. C. kitaibelii} Becherer,{\i  Ber. Schweiz. Bot. Ges.}{\b  43}: 57 (1934) ({\i C. polyphylla} (Waldst. & Kit.) O.E. Schulz, non D. Don). Perennial 20-30(-50) cm; rhizome 3-6 mm in diameter, with concave scale-leaves 5-8 mm. Leaves 3(-5), more or less whorled, pinnate, with 2-6 pairs of serrate, lanceolate leaflets. Petals 15-22 mm, pale yellow, twice as long as the stamens. Siliqua 40-65 × 2·5-3 mm. 2n = 48. {\i Woods. • Alps and adjacent regions; Appennini; N.W. Jugoslavia}. He It Ju.
