\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. C. macrophylla} Willd.,{\i  Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}({\b 1}): 484 (1800). Perennial 30-100 cm, with a long horizontal rhizome c. 2 mm in diameter. Basal leaves 10-25 cm, with 2-4 pairs of subsessile, ovate lateral leaflets and a somewhat larger terminal leaflet; cauline leaves 5-8, with narrower leaflets; leaflets apiculate-crenate to serrate, appressed-hairy. Petals (6-)8-11 mm, pale pink to purple. Siliqua 25-40 × 1·5-2·5 mm, sparsely hairy; beak 1·5-3·5 mm. 2n = 80.{\i  N.E. Russia.} Rs(N, C).
